NCR Corp's Personal Computerdivision said it signed an agreement to distrubute its personalcomputer products to 544 &lt;Computerland Corp> stores in the U.S.    The company said the agreement covers its entire PC line,which will be sold by Computerland franchises, ComputerlandStores Inc, and for major corporate bids, through theComputerland National Accounts Program.    Computerland said it is planning a direct mail campaign andother publicity on its private satellite network to promote theNCR line.    The primary products to be sold by Computerland storesinclude the PC8 AT-compatible unit, the PC6 dual-speed modeland the 2114/PC Retail Management System, according to NCR. Reuter&#3;